title: Animal Waste Disposal System

classifications.description: Hand implements, e.g. litter pickers for picking up excrements
Details characterised by way of removing material the implement being for single use but not glove-like

abstract: An animal waste disposal system, comprising a collection bag having an open end and a closed bottom. A waste removal tool is attached to the closed bottom of the collection bag. The waste removal tool including opposing jaws, with each jaw terminating in a blade portion. The opposing jaws are movable from an open position where the opposing jaws are separated from one another to a closed position where the blade portion of one opposing jaw is in close proximity to the blade portion the other opposing jaw.
claims:
1. An animal waste disposal system, comprising:
a collection bag having an open end and a closed bottom joined by a sidewall to define an interior side and exterior side of the collection bag; a waste removal tool attached to the interior side of the closed bottom of the collection bag, the waste removal tool including a pair of thin opposing jaws joined at one end and having no sidewalls, each jaw including a gripping portion extending from the end, an intermediate portion extending from the gripping portion, and terminating in a blade portion extending from the intermediate portion and angled inward toward the blade portion of the opposing jaw, the opposing jaws being movable from an open position where the opposing jaws are separated from one another to a closed position where the blade portion of one opposing jaw is in close proximity to the blade portion the other opposing jaw.
2. The animal waste disposal system according to claim 1, wherein the waste removal tool is substantially V-shaped.

3. The animal waste disposal system according to claim 1, further comprising a first handle on one of the opposing jaws for receiving a user's fingers and a second handle on the other opposing jaw for receiving the user's thumb.

4. The animal waste disposal system according to claim 1, wherein the waste removal tool is made from a single sheet of flexible material that is folded to permit movement of the opposing jaws relative to one another.
5. The animal waste disposal system according to claim 4, wherein the waste removal tool is made from cardboard.
6. The animal waste disposal system according to claim 1, wherein the waste removal tool is made from heavy paper.
7. The animal waste disposal system according to claim 1, wherein the waste removal tool is made from plastic.
8. The animal waste disposal system according to claim 1, wherein the bag is made from plastic.
9. The animal waste disposal system according to claim 8, wherein the bag is biodegradable.

10. An animal waste disposal system, comprising:
a waste removal tool having a pair of opposing jaws separated by a generally straight intermediate portion, each jaw pivotally connected to an opposing end of the intermediate portion and terminating in a blade portion, the waste removal tool dimensioned to fit within the palm of a user's hand with the user's fingers extending over one of the jaws and the user's thumb extending over the other jaw; the opposing jaws being movable in response to movement of the user's fingers and thumb from an open position where the jaws are separated from one another to a closed position where the blade portion of one opposing jaw is in close proximity to the blade portion the other opposing jaw.
11. The animal waste disposal system according to claim 10, further comprising a collection bag having an open end and a closed bottom.
12. The animal waste disposal system according to claim 11, wherein the closed bottom of the collection bag is positioned within the opposing jaws.
13. The animal waste disposal system according to claim 11, wherein the waste removal tool is attached to the closed bottom of the collection bag.

14. The animal waste disposal system according to claim 10, further comprising a first handle on one of the opposing jaws for receiving a user's fingers and a second handle on the other opposing jaw for receiving the user's thumb.
15. The animal waste disposal system according to claim 10, wherein each jaw includes opposing upstanding sidewalls that are each contiguous with an edge of the blade portion.
16. The animal waste disposal system according to claim 13, wherein the waste removal tool is substantially V-shaped.

17. The animal waste disposal system according to claim 10, wherein the waste removal tool is made from a single sheet of flexible material that is folded to permit movement of the opposing jaws relative to one another.
18. The animal waste disposal system according to claim 10, wherein the waste removal tool is made from cardboard.
19. The animal waste disposal system according to claim 10, wherein the waste removal tool is made from heavy paper.
20. The animal waste disposal system according to claim 10, wherein the waste removal tool is made from plastic.
21. The animal waste disposal system according to claim 11, wherein the bag is made from plastic.
22. The animal waste disposal system according to claim 21, wherein the bag is biodegradable.
